    "created_at": "2015-06-04T07:04:33Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-04T07:04:33Z",
    "body": "I think the behaviour I have suggested should be backwards compatible with existing Electron apps though, I don't understand how it would break them if they're not listening for the `double-clicked` event. It's also possible to have a more explicit `Tray.setIgnoreDoubleClicks()` method but this introduces API bloat.\n"
